Sentencas: La0.6Sr0.4CoO3-delta (LSC)-Ce0.8Gd0.2O2-delta (GDC) nanocomposite materials were prepared by a modified sol-gel method to improve solid oxide fuel cell cathode performance in intermediate temperature.
Titulo: La0.6Sr0.4CoO3-δ -Ce0.8Gd0.2O2-δ nanocomposites prepared by a sol-gel process for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cell cathode applications

Sentencas: Metal acetates precursors and citric acid combined with ethylene glycol as complex agents were used in the sol-gel process.
Titulo: La0.6Sr0.4CoO3-δ -Ce0.8Gd0.2O2-δ nanocomposites prepared by a sol-gel process for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cell cathode applications

Sentencas: Nano foam-like GDC powders were introduced into the sol-gel process to get the nanocomposites with the GDC content in the range of 10-50 wt%.
Titulo: La0.6Sr0.4CoO3-δ -Ce0.8Gd0.2O2-δ nanocomposites prepared by a sol-gel process for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cell cathode applications

Sentencas: In addition, pure LSC nano powders were also synthesized for comparison.
Titulo: La0.6Sr0.4CoO3-δ -Ce0.8Gd0.2O2-δ nanocomposites prepared by a sol-gel process for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cell cathode applications

Sentencas: The crystalline phases, morphologies, and elemental distributions of the pure LSC and LSC-GDC composite powders were characterized, and their electrode performances were investigated with electrochemical impedance spectroscopy.
Titulo: La0.6Sr0.4CoO3-δ -Ce0.8Gd0.2O2-δ nanocomposites prepared by a sol-gel process for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cell cathode applications

Sentencas: The results showed the GDC particles were largely covered by LSC, and the optimal GDC content was 30 wt% for the LSC-GDC electrode performance in this study.
Titulo: La0.6Sr0.4CoO3-δ -Ce0.8Gd0.2O2-δ nanocomposites prepared by a sol-gel process for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cell cathode applications
